		<div class="tab-pane fade" id="compassion">
			<div class='technique-name'>Compassion Fatigue Therapy</div><hr>
			<div class='technique-content'>
				<p>Compassion Fatigue is a state experienced by those helping people in distress. The effects of Compassion Fatigue can cause pain and suffering, therefore it can be helpful to talk about feelings with someone you trust and/or a mental health professional. Our program focuses on helping individuals become more educated about how they are been affected by compassion fatigue, develop healthy lifestyles to decrease the effects of this condition, develop coping strategies decrease symptoms, and identifying resources and networks to prevent stress reactions.</p>

				<p>Common symptoms:
					<ul>
				<li>Chronic physical and emotional exhaustion</li>
				<li>Depersonalization</li>
				<li>Feelings of inequity toward the therapeutic or caregiver relationship</li>
				<li>Irritability</li>
				<li>Feelings of self-contempt</li>
				<li>Difficulty sleeping</li>
				<li>Weight loss</li>
				<li>Headaches</li>
				<li>Poor job satisfaction</li>
			</ul>
			</p>

				<p>Treatment Goals:
					<ul>
				<li>Learning to reducing stressful workloads</li>
				<li>Monitoring sleep patterns</li>
				<li>Taking time to "disconnect" regularly</li>
				<li>Meditation Journaling</li>
				<li>Seeking personal therapy to process work problems</li>
				<li>Regular exercise</li>
			</ul>
			</p>

				<p>Intervention
					<ul>
				<li>Motivation for Change</li>
				<li>High Priority on Self-Care</li>
				<li>Distress Reduction in the Workplace</li>
				<li>Identifying the Situation, Feelings and Thoughts</li>
				<li>Generating Alternative Viewpoints</li>
				<li>Decatastrophizing and De-awfulizing</li>
				<li>Reaching out to support groups and networks</li>
			</ul>
			</p>

